                           <p>The type of paper is “laid” paper. It is thin, and the pulp touches the wires, making a latticework pattern easily seen when the leaf is held against a light. The paper has a watermark. Unlike in this back guard leaf, it is found, throughout the manuscript, in the centre at the place of the binding.</p>
