                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding><p>3 quires of which, the first quire is a quinternion (V), the second and the third quires are quaternion (IV).
1 V (ff. 20) + 2 IV (ff. 16). The stiff covers (boards) at the front and back of the book are attached to the quires by the cords which are secured by means of channelling. Damp leather, which is folded over the edges of the boards forming a turn-ins and glued down, covers the boards and the spine. Pastedowns of the initial and final bifolio onto the inside of the board conceal this mechanism (binding and channelling). Not numbered guard leaves. On the recto of the first guard leaf, the title of the Grammar appears, while on the verso there is the Preface.</p></binding>
